        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2011752167" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6491843884333427889">Free Will is a short but informative book (judging by its length calling it an essay would probably be more accurate) looking to prove that free will is an illusion, and I have to say, it managed to convince me. <br/>Despite the daunting subject, Haris&apos; ideas are clear and easy to grasp which is something I really appreciate in non-fiction. So many authors get so tangled in their ideas that they forget that what they&apos;re writing isn&apos;t meant just for them. <br/>It was great, food for thought for a very long</span>
  <span id="freeText6491843884333427889" style="display:none">Free Will is a short but informative book (judging by its length calling it an essay would probably be more accurate) looking to prove that free will is an illusion, and I have to say, it managed to convince me. <br />Despite the daunting subject, Haris' ideas are clear and easy to grasp which is something I really appreciate in non-fiction. So many authors get so tangled in their ideas that they forget that what they're writing isn't meant just for them. <br />It was great, food for thought for a very long time. I highly recommend it.</span>
